02:12.345 --> 02:15.869
That was mighty fine fiddling, and I know most of the old-timers out there.

02:15.909 --> 02:17.931
In fact, I believe all of them enjoyed that.

02:18.312 --> 02:18.952
Uncle Penn.

02:20.795 --> 02:25.360
Friends, I wanted to talk to you just a little dab-dab and a half, two dabs here about the forestry boys.

02:25.380 --> 02:27.943
Now, whether they're your local foresters,

02:27.974 --> 02:32.955
they work with the state or uncle sam it don't make any difference they're all human beings

02:33.425 --> 02:44.257
And with special training, they've all got special training, special ability to do the job of keeping the forest green and growing and safe from fire.

02:44.738 --> 02:52.867
They're really doing one of the most important jobs there is in the United States, and that is keeping fire out of the woods.

02:52.887 --> 03:01.457
They're trying to keep fire out of the woods, but still there's some people that'll be careless with their matches and cigarettes and let the fire get out.

03:01.437 --> 03:04.501
And that causes these boys to have to work night and day.

03:05.582 --> 03:10.429
And, friends, I've got an interest in this thing, and I know most of you out there listening have.

03:10.769 --> 03:12.231
In fact, all of you have.

03:12.992 --> 03:14.654
You just get careless, that's all.

03:14.674 --> 03:15.836
That's the only thing about it.

03:16.356 --> 03:19.681
And I want you to look on to these boys as just one of you.

03:19.701 --> 03:23.125
I've known of cases where some of the boys would have on maybe a necktie.

03:23.678 --> 03:32.153
And some local guy that lived out there in the woods somewhere would poke fun at him just because he had on a necktie.

03:32.533 --> 03:37.782
Well, that don't make any difference whether he's got on a necktie or hip boots and red pajamas.

03:37.822 --> 03:39.646
That still don't make any difference.

03:39.666 --> 03:40.808
He's still a human being.

03:40.868 --> 03:42.210
He has special training.

03:42.190 --> 03:44.232
to do this firefighting job.

03:44.252 --> 03:54.222
As I told you in a past program that I have been on cases, been on fires where a man called himself back firing and he burnt off the whole country.

03:54.622 --> 03:57.465
Well, these boys have been taught different.

03:57.485 --> 04:02.911
They know where and when and how to set these fires and they need your help.

04:02.931 --> 04:08.316
It's just like being a game warden or being a traffic cop or being any

04:08.650 --> 04:12.356
officer, I'd say, they can't do the job by themselves.

04:13.298 --> 04:15.962
You've got to cooperate with them.

04:17.104 --> 04:19.608
Now, I've got some good examples.

04:20.209 --> 04:25.798
Some of the high schools are farming local forest protection crews.

04:25.818 --> 04:30.085
They're trying to help prevent these forest fires, woods fires.

04:30.352 --> 04:46.915
Even if more folks would just help mop up and patrol a burned area where the fire's already burned after the fire crews have got the fire controlled, if more people would take an interest in it and try to keep it from jumping the fire lines and getting out again, friends, that would help a lot.

04:46.975 --> 04:49.238
You just don't realize how much it would help.

04:49.218 --> 04:57.108
When there's been a long drought, dry season, no rain and all that, and they're out fighting fire night and day, you just don't know.

04:57.128 --> 04:59.932
If you'd follow these boys around a while, then you'd know.

05:00.433 --> 05:01.734
That's when they need your help.

05:02.155 --> 05:03.977
That's when they need it most.

05:03.997 --> 05:06.420
And they need a helping hand.

05:07.502 --> 05:15.512
And really, really understanding of a tough job that they have to do, it's all a matter of understanding, really, friends.

05:16.167 --> 05:18.073
And I got a story about that.

05:18.093 --> 05:19.879
But first, here's the next tune.

05:19.899 --> 05:21.645
And I believe Charlie's going to sing it.

05:22.187 --> 05:24.675
It's a little thing called the Tennessee Saturday Night.

05:31.422 --> 05:52.519
